title: Cults, Live From Le Poisson Rouge
description: The New York City synth-rock duo of singer Madeline Follin and keyboardist Brian Oblivion expanded to a raucous five-piece band for NPR Music's Oct. 16 showcase at (Le) Poisson Rouge in New York. Watch a nine-song set including cuts from the new album, Static, just one day after its release. "High Road" "Slow Song" "Abducted" "Always Forever" "Were Before" "You Know What I Mean" "I Can Hardly Make You Mine" "Go Outside" "Keep Your Head Up"
